@startuml
title Part 3 — Dashboard Runtime Flow (React + AWS Cognito + Spring Boot API)

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica Neue"
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam roundCorner 10
skinparam ArrowColor #34495E
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.1
skinparam sequence {
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #34495E
  ParticipantBorderColor #2C3E50
  ParticipantFontColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontStyle bold
  ActorBackgroundColor #34495E
  ActorBorderColor #2C3E50
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  GroupBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  GroupBorderColor #90A4AE
  GroupHeaderFontColor #2C3E50
  DividerBackgroundColor #34495E
  DividerFontColor #FFFFFF
}

actor User

participant UI as "React UI\n(Browser SPA)"

box "AWS" #FFF3E0
  participant Cognito as "Cognito User Pool\neu-central-1_k4a9qUIbH"
end box

box "Microsoft Azure" #E3F2FD
  participant API as "Spring Boot API\n(p3-api)"
  database DB as "PostgreSQL\nlatest_data / historical_data"
end box

== Login (OIDC Authorization Code Flow) ==
User -> UI: Open app
UI -> Cognito: 1. signinRedirect (authorize, response_type=code)
Cognito --> UI: 2. Redirect back with authorization code
UI -> Cognito: 3. Exchange code for tokens
Cognito --> UI: 4. id_token + access_token\n(claims: cognito:groups, custom:device_id)

== Dashboard data request ==
UI -> API: 5. OPTIONS /api/dashboard-data (CORS preflight)
API --> UI: 6. 200 — Allow-Origin + Allow-Headers: Authorization

UI -> API: 7. GET /api/dashboard-data\nAuthorization: Bearer <id_token>
activate API
API -> Cognito: 8. Fetch JWKS (cached)
Cognito --> API: 9. Public keys
API -> API: 10. Validate JWT (signature + issuer-uri)
API -> API: 11. Map cognito:groups → ROLE_Admin / ROLE_User\nread custom:device_id

alt Admin (ROLE_Admin)
  API -> DB: 12a. latestRepo.findAll() + historicalRepo.findAll()
  activate DB
  DB --> API: 13a. all latest[] + historical[]
  deactivate DB
  API --> UI: 14a. 200 OK\n{ role:"admin", latest:[...], historical:[...] }

else User with custom:device_id
  API -> DB: 12b. latestRepo.findById(deviceId)\nhistoricalRepo.findByDeviceId(deviceId)
  activate DB
  DB --> API: 13b. latest (0..1) + historical[]
  deactivate DB
  API --> UI: 14b. 200 OK\n{ role:"user", device_id, latest:[...], historical:[...] }

else User without device claim
  API --> UI: 14c. 403 Forbidden\n(missing custom:device_id)
end
deactivate API

== Rendering ==
UI -> UI: 15. dataProcessor → table + line/bar charts
UI -> User: 16. Render Energy Analytics Dashboard

== Logout (OIDC) ==
User -> UI: Click "Sair"
UI -> Cognito: 17. signoutRedirect (revoke tokens)
Cognito --> UI: 18. Redirect to post_logout_redirect_uri

@enduml
